Workers affiliated with the National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) downed their tools last month demanding better pay. CAPE TOWN - Hisense Atlantis is operating at full tilt again after a weeks-long strike saw production grind to a halt. Workers affiliated with the National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) downed their tools last month demanding better pay. They wanted a 15% wage hike. After intense negotiations, both parties agreed on a 7% increase for the next two years. Numsa's Vuyo Lufele explained the other benefits that workers had gained. "We have agreed on three days of extra leave after five years with the company and also we agreed on a bonus that 40% now must be a guaranteed bonus for the end of the year."